The paper deals with algorithmic aspects of a graph problem, specifically the Semitotal Domination problem. This problem involves finding a dominating set of minimum cardinality in a graph where every vertex in the set is within distance 2 of another vertex in the set. This problem is related to topics such as graph theory, computational geometry, and combinatorics, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.CC, and cs.GT. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper. Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely as they specifically deal with algorithmic aspects of graph problems.
